&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MariaDB MaxScale&lt;/strong&gt; is a database proxy that manages traffic between applications and MariaDB server clusters. It functions as an intermediary layer to provide high availability, scalability, and&lt;br&gt;load balancing. Because applications connect to MaxScale as if it were a MariaDB server, complex operations—such as read-write splitting, query limiting, and transparent failover—can&lt;br&gt;be implemented without modifying the application.&lt;/p&gt;
